reviewText: A few weeks ago, I got the five workout TurboJam set that includes "Learn & Burn", a 20 minute workout, and Cardio Party I.  I'm loving Turbo Jam, and highly recommend it.  I ordered Cardio Party 3 because I was doing Cardio Party I everyday and recognized that I'd want to rotate some other videos in to avoid boredom.While I enjoy Cardio Party 3, I think if you start with it you won't enjoy Turbo Jam.  Insofar as Turbo Jam has weaknesses, they are more noticeable here, and the strengths are harder to see.  Chalene Johnson doesn't use the music as well here, and sometimes it seemed like she was fighting the beat.  She does more high impact, and she expects you pick up a lot more without cuing.  She's also a bit more annoying, with more chatter and an overly cute little skirt.  That's all fine if you're adding this DVD to a Turbo Jam collection, but not a good way to start.The five workout set that comes with Cardio Party has a slow section that teaches the moves and two very manageable workouts for getting started.  Then Cardio Party 1 is a lot of fun, works well with the music, and is a better way to get going.An update to this review:  after quite a bit more TurboJam, I came back to Cardio Party 3.  While my original review stands, once you are good at TurboJam and trying to maintain some variety, this could become a favorite.  It is higher energy than the others, and harder to learn.  As I've gotten better at TurboJam, and my workout requirements more demanding, the challenge of Cardio Party 3 makes it a favorite.  I still struggle with how the class is moving to the music, but as I learn the routine I'm able to look away and concentrate on the beat myself.  I'd buy this one last...by then you'll be ready for it.

reviewText: I'm not going to go through details about this video, but let me just say I think it is awesome.  I regularly do Punch, Kick, and Jam, and Cardio Party.  I bought this one and let it lay around for awhile, did it once got mad and gave up.  Some of the moves are a little different and too dancey, and she adds on a lot in some parts out of the blue.  But, about a week a go I felt a little bored with the others and pulled it out again.  I've done it 5 times since.  It's so fun and the moves and music are a blast.  Once you get the other DVDs down pat, this one really shouldn't be that hard.  There are a few moves here and there that she does where you're confused a little, but like Queen Chalene mentions, you're still burning calories making mistakes.  You'll get it soon enough.  The only reason I give it 4 out of 5 is Chalene is a little bit less supportive and almost a tad bit cocky in this video.  I don't know why this bugs me, it just does.  But don't let it make you not do this video.  It's so fun!
summary: More Fun, After You Learn the Steps

reviewText: This is the fourth dvd I've purchased in the Turbo Jam series. I really liked cardio party 2 and wanted another dance/kick/punch dvd to change it up. First this video is 50 minutes. I usually like to work out for 30 (40 max). Secondly the music is alot of remixed stuff from other videos. Remixes... I don't like. At one point it sounds like someone is rapping Foxy Brown style. I don't know... I found that highly annoying. The moves are more of the same but the combinations are very confusing and difficult to follow. Difficult for me, but also the people working out with Chalene. I see alot of them "catching" up to Chalene and they practiced how much before the taping of the video? At one point I was just doing the bob/weave and watching to see where I needed to be. I guess at least I was still moving and burning calories. The turbo is the same turbo from the Fatblaster video. Luckily I liked that combination so half way through the video I found a part I really liked! Yea.I've been doing turbo jam on and off for 3 years. If your purchasing this video be ready for a long work out, annoying music and flailing arms. I highly recommend Fatblaster, Lower Body Jam, and Cardio Party 2,

reviewText: I have always loved BeachBody workouts because they work. I absolutely love Turbo Fire because its upbeat, the music is fun and Chalene (the instructor) is so fun! So after reading about Turbo Jam and how well it works, I decided to look the videos up on Youtube, and thought they looked like lots of fun as well. I like mixing up my workout routine and this would be perfect! These are not as fast paced on TurboFire, but they are just as fun! The music is great, I stay in my fat burning zone more, and the moves are easy to learn. Chalenes cues are great, better than they are in TurboFire. After you learn the moves, the workouts become funner and funner. I would recommend starting with TurboJam first, then moving up to TurboFire since TurboFire is so advanced. Although I started with TurboFire then went to TurboJam, it works either way.I also want to say that anyone that is looking to thin out their legs, saddle bags, muffin top and gain ab definition should look into TurboJam since this workout repeats alot of moves that target those areas. Also, have fun and let loose when she gets to the "dance scene" it makes the workout that much more fun. :-)

reviewText: First off, let me just say that this video is really fun. It's everything CP2 isn't - high impact and upbeat. CP2 is fine, it just seemed less intense than CP1, which I was not expecting. This is the 3rd mix, so I wouldn't recommend starting off with this one too soon. Get to know the first 5 workouts, and maybe the Punch, Kick, and Jam DVD and the Fat Blaster DVD. This DVD seems to be for an experienced TJ'er who really knows all the moves and is looking to mix it up a bit. Chalene doesn't cue as much here because, hey, if you've been doing this for a while, you don't need all that extra help on the routines anyway. Chalene really lets loose and enjoys herself, which makes me want to let loose, too. Another thing I love - the core section in the middle of the video before the Turbo. It's pretty intense cardio core work - lots of wheels, etc. All in all, this is a great addition to your TJ collection if you've been doing it for a while and want a fresh new mix to throw in your rotation.
summary: CP3 - Great for an experienced TJ'er
